<title>How It Works</title>
</head>

<body>
<p><strong>Overview<br />
</strong>The Life Underground Tour is broken into 2 rounds of voting. In the first round of voting, September 1st to November 15th, all registered bands will by vying for a position in the top 10 for each region.All voting will be performed by registered users of Best of Bands. There are no judges, therefore the bands that get their fans to vote the most will win. </p>
<p>After the top 10 are selected from each region a promotional CD, consisting of a track from each of the top 10 semi-finalists, will be distributed regionally.. </p>
<p>Beginning December 1st the top 6 finalists from each region will submit a video for The Life Underground Tour's Virtual Tour. The Virtual Tour will allow all of Best of Bands users to watch videos from all of our semi-finalists. During the Virutal Tour there will be additional activities.</p>
<p>Once the Virtual Tour has run it's course the second round of voting will begin. All of the semi-finalists will compete for the number 1 spot. Remember, there are no judeges except for your fans. At the end of the second round of voting there will be 6 bands. These bands, chosen by you, will go on to tour the US. With stops in each bands hometown, along with military bases the LIfe Underground Tour promises to be rockin' time.</p>
<p><strong>Who Can Enter? </strong><br />
Registration is open to U.S. bands with all members over 18.</p>
<p><strong>How do I register? </strong><br />
You can register by clicking on the Register link and filling out the form. There is also a $25 registration fee which may be paid by credit card, check, or money order. $1 from each registration will be donated to MusicForTroops.com</p>
<p><strong>Can I enter in more than one region?</strong><br />
  Yes, you may register in as many regions as you would like. Just remember that there is a $25 registration fee for each registration.</p>
<p><strong>Who chooses the winners?  </strong><br />
Registered members of Best of Bands are the people who will choose the winners. Every band should enlist every single fan to vote for them every day. </p>
<p><strong>How does the voting work? <br />
</strong>Each member of Best of Bands will be allowed to cast one vote per artist in any 24-hour period. While you may only vote for a specific band once a day you are allowed to cast votes for multiple bands.</p>
<p><strong>How will people know to vote for me?</strong> <strong><br />
</strong>Each participating band will have a voting icon placed on their Best of Bands profile page. Also, there will be widgets available to place on all of your websites.</p>
<p><strong>How can I increase my votes?</strong><br />
Spread the word - anywhere and everywhere. Use the widgets provided. Put them on your sites, in your emails...get your fans to use them in their emails. Announce your participation at your live shows. Send an S.O.S. to your mailing list. Put it in your newsletters, your flyers, CD inserts. Tell your friends that if they love you, they'll vote for you. Call in favors from people who owe your. Go to the nearest mountaintop and shout out your band's name for the whole town to hear. Go on YouTube. Go on MySpace. Tell the world to &quot;Get Busy!&quot; and cast their votes for your band.</p>
<p><strong>Who do I contact with questions?</strong><br />
If you have any further questions, email contest@bestofbands.com</p>
